{
  "rationale": "Built on engine-calibration's anchor-fit coefficients (lowest MAE) and patched with the systematic failures found by re-simulating all four proposals against reconstructed anchor rows. Key fixes: (1) cooling no longer leaks onto fruit/refreshing — driven only by role=cooling + mint/menthol/ice keywords, so Pear/Lychee/Cola stay 2-3 while Mint hits ~8-10; (2) heatTolerance base raised and tea/cooling penalties softened so mint/fruit don't crater (Mint 5, Lychee 4.7) while tea still dips; (3) freshness base lifted and cream penalty eased so Coconut/Cola don't hit 0; (4) sweetness penalties trimmed so tea/lime keep a 1-3 floor instead of 0; (5) bitterness tea-stacking reduced (Earl Grey 4.3 not 7); (6) added the 5 secondary/layer fields from data-engineering + product with anchor-aware tuning. Coverage: all 18 derived fields, all 16 CSV role tokens. Result: MAE 0.80 across 121 (anchor,dim) pairs, 13 residuals >1.5 (most barely over, e.g. Coconut body 7.7 vs 6, Mint cooling clamp 9.8 vs 8). Robust to nulls: every map omits unmatched keys, base anchors a sane mid value. [post-validation patch by implementer, grounded in knowledge.md: freshness now treats mint/menthol/ice and role=cooling as POSITIVE (清涼=空調感=freshness); the council had inverted this, cratering Mint freshness. Re-validated against anchors after the change.]",
